I definitely don't want to lose.

53
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,680
Hey!

54
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:26,360
Festival Guy in Sabae!

55
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:29,000
- Bring it on.
- You waited too long.

56
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,000
Our guide this time

57
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,880
is Director-general
of Fukui Optical Association,

58
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:35,720
Mr Yasutaka Shimamura.

59
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,600
Say it again. What association?

60
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:41,480
I'm Fukui Optical Association's
Shimamura.

61
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:42,600
Yes, glasses!

62
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:45,280
- It's a nice frame.
- Thank you.

63
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,960
Please tell me what you take
seriously about glasses.

64
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:51,120
It looks heavy, but it's
surprisingly light when you wear it.

65
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:53,400
The glasses are light
when you wear them.

66
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:57,440
My facial features are quite close
together in the centre.

67
00:02:57,520 --> 00:03:01,160
I want them to look wider apart,
so I use a bigger frame.

68
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:04,080
Scattering glasses.

69
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:07,120
- The festival held in Sabae here.
- Yes?

70
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,760
Is it dangerous?

71
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,960
- It isn't dangerous.
- No, right?

72
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,920
Can I ask the name of the event?

73
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,800
It's called Megamori.

74
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:16,400
What? After all these...

75
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:18,760
It's food?

76
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,160
Megamori?

77
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,760
They go to the venue that will be
the stage of the battle.

78
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:27,080
Mr Miyagawa,
please have a look at that.

79
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:32,480
- What?
- What did Miyagawa see?

80
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:37,360
It's men who are wearing
many pairs of glasses.

81
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:40,520
Megamori means a lot of glasses?

82
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:44,480
Megamori is an event
that participants compete to see

83
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,600
who wears more pairs of glasses
on their face.

84
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:50,800
80 percent of the glasses frames
made in Japan

85
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:52,840
are produced in Sabae City.

86
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:55,840
It's one of the three major glasses
frames production area in the world.

87
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,880
Glasses Festival is held every year,

88
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:02,160
Megamori started in 2014
as an event of the festival.

89
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:05,840
But it was cancelled last year
because of the pandemic.

90
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:10,280
People in the city pray
it'll be held this year.

91
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:14,040
That's many pairs of glasses!
Amazing!

92
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,840
- It's exciting, right?
- Yes.

93
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:19,200
It makes people smile,
from children to adults.

94
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:20,320
It looks so stupid.

95
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,360
The rule is very simple.

96
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:26,600
Put as many pairs of glasses in
the basket as you can on your face

97
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:28,720
in the one-minute time limit.

98
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:31,200
Stop for five seconds when it ends,

99
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:33,360
and the number of glasses that stay
will be recorded.

100
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,320
If they all fall when you say stop

101
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,240
and three pairs stay,
that'll be the record.

102
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,680
Three will be the record.

103
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:43,480
The way they count the number
is also full of love for glasses.

104
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:48,000
The Glasses Festival is set up
as a festival to thank our glasses,

105
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:50,360
so we fold them one by one
and say thank you.

106
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:53,560
We say thank you,
and continue to count.

107
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,240
Fold, and "thank you."

108
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:57,600
Thank you.

109
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,920
- Can I ask, Mr Shimamura?
- Go ahead.

110
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:03,760
How many pairs did the champion wear
to win?

111
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:04,960
35 pairs.

112
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,720
What?

113
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,400
My enemy is strong.

114
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:11,160
Now, he'll do some practise.

115
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:14,560
Pile them tidily,
one above the other.

116
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:17,440
You have to pile them up precisely.

117
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,520
This festival is so fun!

118
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:22,280
First, he tries it in 30 seconds.

119
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,680
Ready, go.

120
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:29,280
Miyagawa is putting
the glasses on smoothly,

121
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:30,920
but...

122
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:35,400
It falls if he doesn't put them on
carefully enough.

123
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,360
Not the pair that fell.

124
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,360
- It's difficult.
- Yes.

125
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:43,000
They barely hang there.

126
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,080
Five seconds left.

127
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,720
What...

128
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:53,080
Two, one.

129
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:55,400
Stop. Like this.

130
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:56,440
That's 30 seconds?

131
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,680
He'll stop for five seconds
after it ends.

132
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:02,040
I'll take them all off.

133
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:07,680
Didn't I put them on my face
surprisingly tidily?

134
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,400
Thank you.

135
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:13,240
Do not forget to express gratitude
to the glasses.

136
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:14,320
- Thank you.
- It's nice.

137
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,040
13 pairs.

138
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,320
We'll double it, so it's 26 pairs.

139
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,200
I need 10 more pairs
to catch up with the champion.

140
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:24,200
But it was only 30 seconds,

141
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,800
so it's going to get difficult
to find places to put them on.

142
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:29,480
It won't double just because
I did it for 30 seconds.

143
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,400
That's right.

144
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:33,560
I... Well, I want to win.

145
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:38,880
For example, it's not right
to put them here,

146
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:41,560
but it's quicker to wear them
than taking the time.

147
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:43,800
I see.

148
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,800
This festival is so fun.

149
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:50,840
He tries it in one minute,
like the real competition.

150
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,000
Start.

151
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:56,440
The record of the champion
is 35 pairs,

152
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,600
what does that look like?

153
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:01,280
I'll put them on quickly.
I guess I shouldn't overdo it.

154
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:06,000
The glasses are piled up tidily.

155
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,800
It looks good.

156
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,640
The difficult part of this

157
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:15,960
